@electric_forest !!!! WE’RE ON THE BILL!!!! 🚨😭

Long time coming, they said let’s make it official at one of the biggest parties in my home state also the first festival I ever went to as Rothbury ‘09 setting the stage for what will be FT @ EF ‘23 BABY!!!! ⚡️🌲❤️ tix in bio

📸: @sattadondada @isometricmag

A lot of hard work went into 2022 and a lot of music and love came out!!!! 💞 Also a lot of firsts: I released my first dedicated experimental jungly / breaks type album in the form of the Nineteen Ninety LP and also my first dedicated four on the floor tech / housey type EP in the form of Liquefaction, both on my label Freddy Todd Music. I collabed with the homie @wreckno for one of the acid house songs off that and also made an appearance on Detroit’s own @golfclapdet on his Mind Games release via our tune “Brackish”. I also realized I’m definitely going to form a new alias to channel my house vibe (more on that in 2023) while keeping FT a friendly place for the never-ending experimental funky jazzy bass end of things. 

However, in the bass world - 2022 was not lacking for ya boye: the 130 bpm bass blaster single “Water Worker” saw a mid-summer release on the dude @mersivsoundproject label @morflorecords followed by another 130 bpm bass adventure “Been Up, Been Down” on FTM in November (that I wrote via inspiration after my 2022 @electric_forest afters appearances). To wrap it all up with a nice bow, I also was informed by Spotify that for the first time ever, I cracked 1 million plays within the year of 2022. And that’s just one app!! 

All I have to say is I am so thankful and grateful that I not only have the privilege, wherewithal, ability, and technology to be able to CREATE like this but I am SO lucky to have beautiful humans who actually LISTEN to the weird ideas I cook up in my home-lab. Thanks to everyone who’s been here since day one and thanks to any new travelers who may have joined me recently on this journey. And I’m SO excited for 2023. If y’all only knew what I’m currently preparing sonically in almost every direction from bass to house to jazz to rnb to rap to ghettotech to drum and bass to jungle to pop to wave to everything psychedelic in between and around the corner (I will say to my bass music fans, my satchel of IDs is getting LARGE). I love music!!!! ✨✌️❤️

Much love & see u next year
-FT

Hello friends! Big news: The world debut solo set of my house music alias @heatline__ is going down right after Movement this Saturday at midnight in the technotropolis of Detroit 👉🔥👈 

Announcing this new project is very special to me growing up a Detroitboy being blessed with the Concrete Heartbeat reverberating sounds of DEMF / Movement fest since I was a young lad, very formative years..

Fast forward to me traveling & living around the country for a decade making & playing bass music when I found my way back home in 2019 the foundations of all the Heatline tunes started formulating, the oozing vibe of house & techno was always inescapably infectious. Since then, making hella bass tunes as Freddy Todd and an almost equal amount of specifically different house music tunes, a reservoir was needed and the channel of Heatline was forged ♨️

Tomorrow I’ll be showcasing a ton of original new Heatline material alongside some favorites and classics, swipe to slide 5 for a preview of “Gamma Drama”

ps. make sure to stick around 4 @blaapband after 😜

SO MUCH LOVE ❤️
- FT / HL

📸: @maxdashevsky

OKAY 2023!!!! This past year was full of some momentous and monumental moments for yer boye ushering in what is sure to be the set up for an insane 2024, in no particular order:

1. 3rd time officially playing @electric_forest & biggest forest set yet
2. one of my besties @ofthetreesmusic & I throwing a sold out unofficial Movement afters with @blaapband & @defineeverythingfuture ‘s first time in Detroit (ID: BLAAP - Mushrooms)
3. Opening for @shponglemusic dressed as Neo at The Fillmore in Denver
4. Launching my house music alias / project @heatline__ (set is on DEF’s YouTube with 10 unreleased tunes)
5. Got to b2b with the actual legend @si_bonobo in Detroit
6. Released “Sony Toprano” single with @chef_boyarbeatz 
7. Released “Forest Temple” single @common_creation 
8. Released my record labels first vinyl on Freddy Todd Music “Moonflavours II” & oversold-out the campaign 
9. Got to play one of the last @griz finalés in beautiful AZ
10. Got to jam on keytar with some insanely dope musicians like @gspacemusic 

These don’t cover everything and are just some snippets butttt I wanted to say thank you for sticking around and supporting the project thus far.
